			<div id="post-2980" class="post-2980 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-photography tag-camera tag-dslr tag-light tag-painting tag-photography tag-slr tag-steel tag-wool">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.zxzxzx.info/night-photography/" title="Permalink to Night Photography" rel="bookmark">Night Photography</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="https://www.zxzxzx.info/night-photography/" title="1:18 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">February 14, 2018</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://www.zxzxzx.info/author/zxzxzx/" title="View all posts by zxzxzx">zxzxzx</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>Just thought I&#8217;d share some photos I took with a mate many nights ago now. I enjoy photography as a hobby and occasionally experiment with new techniques &#8211; it&#8217;s also one of the reasons I enjoy travelling.</p>
<p>We went out to Maroubra (a coastal Sydney suburb) to take these in the evening. It was our first time experimenting with steel wool in photography so we wanted a nice backdrop in all of our shots. This involved using long exposures of 10 ~ 20 seconds. One of us lit up fine steel wool that was stuffed into a metal whisk and swung it around while the other focused the shot and hit the buttons. As the wool burns and the sparks fly out, it doesn&#8217;t last more than around 20 seconds anyway. The effect that you see is a result of the camera&#8217;s shutter being open for the duration of the motion, and thus it captures the moving elements of the image as a trail.</p>
<p class="jetpack-slideshow-noscript robots-nocontent">This slideshow requires JavaScript.</p><div id="gallery-2980-1-slideshow" class="slideshow-window jetpack-slideshow slideshow-black" data-trans="fade" data-autostart="1" data-gallery="[{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-2.jpg?fit=640%2C480\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2982&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (2)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-3.jpg?fit=640%2C360\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2983&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (3)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-5.jpg?fit=640%2C480\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2985&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (5)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-1.jpg?fit=640%2C360\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2981&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (1)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-7.jpg?fit=640%2C427\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2986&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (7)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-4.jpg?fit=640%2C360\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2984&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (4)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-10.jpg?fit=640%2C483\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2987&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (10)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;}]" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageGallery"></div>
<p>For anyone interested in trying this, remember to tie your whisk to a sturdy string! I ended up losing my whisk because the string snapped&#8230;so we had to drive a fair distance to the nearest supermarket for another one.</p>
<p>Light painting is a similar technique which involves moving a glowing object in a long exposure against a dark background to trace out an image. Using the LED light on the back of our phones, we were able to use almost the same settings to capture a few of these, though they&#8217;re not quite as spectacular as the steel wool ones.</p>
<p class="jetpack-slideshow-noscript robots-nocontent">This slideshow requires JavaScript.</p><div id="gallery-2980-2-slideshow" class="slideshow-window jetpack-slideshow slideshow-black" data-trans="fade" data-autostart="1" data-gallery="[{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-9.jpg?fit=640%2C427\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2993&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (9)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-8.jpg?fit=640%2C427\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2992&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (8)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/www.zxzxzx.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SteelWoolLightPainting-6.jpg?fit=640%2C464\u0026ssl=1&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2991&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SteelWoolLightPainting (6)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;itemprop&quot;:&quot;image&quot;}]" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageGallery"></div>
<p>Anyone else into photography? I love doing landscapes, though lately I&#8217;ve been getting more interested in long night exposures and star trails.</p>
